text: [Music]
last week the YouTube channel hit
100,000 subscribers so I wanted to send
a huge thank you out to everybody at the
end of the day this is just a big group
project between you the community and
myself with a goal of building something
that we can all benefit from and learn
from and I'm also super grateful for how
nice this community is as you probably
know a lot of YouTube comments can get
pretty ugly and even asking questions on
stack Overflow can get pretty ugly if
you ask the wrong thing but I feel like
this has been one of the most helpful
and polite communities that I've ever
been a part of so I feel like I have to
be one of the luckiest YouTubers out
there my original plan for reaching this
Milestone was to give away a t-shirt or
maybe a Tesla but based on your feedback
it seems like a better option might be
to offer a full free course and that's
what I intend to do I already have plans
sketched out for a code This Not That
full course that just covers the
fundamentals of JavaScript even though
most apps in the real world are going to
require a framework knowing how to do
things in vanilla JavaScript is very
liberating as a developer that course
will be entirely free and you can look
forward to it shipping sometime in March
but there's a few other things on the
road map that will come first I have a
payments course that is underway right
now and will be released by the end of
this month and also now that ionic 4 is
out I'm going to update the ionic 4
Master course and bring that over to
fireship and also I have a native app in
development for fireship and that app
will provide supplemental content like
quizzes for the actual courses
themselves and of course you can expect
a full flutter course shortly after that
app is released the last thing I want to
talk about is the migration process for
pro members of angular Firebase to
fireship I built an entirely new
membership platform for reasons that I
explained in the previous channel update
and it's the pro membership that really
makes this project sustainable so doing
a migration like this is very risky for
me and very annoying for you to make it
as painless as possible I'm just going
to Discount the out of the new
membership for existing members if
you're a lifetime member you'll
automatically get lifetime access on
fireship if you're a monthly or
quarterly member you'll get a discount
code for 75% off of the membership rate
that means you'll be able to lock in a
rate of around $5 per month that gives
you access to all of the premium courses
and pro features that I produce in the
future it's probably not a great
business idea but it's something I feel
good about doing just because that early
Pro membership support is what really
allowed this channel to flourish so if
you're an existing angular Firebase PR
member you'll get that email most likely
sometime next week I'll go ahead and
wrap up the update there if you have any
questions reach out on slack thanks for
watching and I will talk to you soon
[Music]
